  "title": "structure coordinator",
  "description": "<p>• Monitor consultant's design progress as per submission/ detail design schedule agreed. Study consultants' design drawings and highlight the missing information, design clashes and design inconveniences for construction.</p><p>• Manage the project's design coordination works. Liaise with Clients, Consultants and Subcontractors to ensure the smooth progress of the coordination. Ensure the information between different disciplines are communicated and discussed among the team.</p><p>• Manage the project’s drawing coordination in between disciplines and sub-contractors’ drawings.</p><p>• Manage the project’s drawing schedule, to ensure timely issuance of drawings for construction.</p><p>• Work with BIM modeller/drafter on shop drawings preparation, to capture all detail dimensions and settings. Must be able to convey technical information to BIM modeller/ drafter via sketches. Must be able to study and understand technical drawings independently without the drafter's assistance. Must be able to identify the critical technical information/sections that need to be generated for construction usage and technical resolution.</p><p>• Work with the construction team and sub-cons to prepare and submit for approval the construct i) material submission, ii) material specification submission, iii) method statement and iv) specialist trade sub-con shop drawings.</p><p>• Address and resolve technical issues raised by the construction and consultant's teams, through clear communication and good documentation.<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>• Degree in Civil Engineering or Architectural discipline</p><p>• At least 3 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.</p><p>• Experience in residential project will be advantageous.</p>",
